---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services"
  description="One integrated service, delivered in phases across the life of your mortgage: equity building while you are strong, foreclosure protection when hardship threatens, a realtor-led sale if keeping the home is not realistic, and foreclosure recovery if foreclosure still happens."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="What we do"
    title="One service. Delivered in phases. Across the life of your mortgage."
    description="Equity Guardians is not four products in a bundle. It is one service that begins while you are strong, adapts when hardship arrives, and stays with you if things get worse."
  />

  <section id="how-it-works" class="section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
        <h2>Three coordinated roles, one integrated service.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Every family is supported by three roles working together. Real estate matters go through
          your Buyer's Realtor. Legal matters go through your Legal Team. And a dedicated Case
          Manager keeps the process moving so nothing falls through the cracks.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="roles-grid mt-4">
        <div class="role-card reveal">
          <span class="role-eyebrow">The cornerstone</span>
          <h3>Legal Team</h3>
          <p>
            A nationwide network of vetted foreclosure-defense attorneys. When hardship threatens
            the home, they review notices and deadlines, communicate with your servicer, and
            evaluate every legal option available in your state. Legal advice and representation
            come from the attorney under a separate engagement, not from Equity Guardians.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="role-card reveal">
          <span class="role-eyebrow">The foundation</span>
          <h3>Buyer's Realtor</h3>
          <p>
            A licensed real estate professional who purchases coverage for the family out of their
            commission at closing, then stays involved for the life of the mortgage. If a sale
            becomes the right move, the same Realtor who helped the family buy the home is
            positioned to help them sell it, rent, and buy again.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="role-card reveal">
          <span class="role-eyebrow">The coordination layer</span>
          <h3>Case Manager</h3>
          <p>
            The family's single point of contact. The Case Manager coordinates the team, keeps
            everyone informed, connects the family with an appropriate attorney, and arranges
            payment of the attorney's retainer through the program. Not a lawyer, not a broker, no
            legal or real estate advice.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="phase-01">
    <div class="container service-block reveal">
      <div class="service-copy">
        <span class="motto">
          <span class="motto-n">01</span>
          <span class="motto-t">While You're Strong</span>
        </span>
        <h2>Build equity faster. Reduce interest. Create a cushion before hardship ever arrives.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Most foreclosure companies wait for a crisis. Equity Guardians starts on day one. While
          the family is financially strong, we help them build equity faster, reduce the long-term
          interest they will pay, and create a cushion large enough to change what is possible if
          hardship ever comes.
        </p>
        <p class="lede">
          A homeowner with meaningful equity has more ways to avoid foreclosure altogether. They
          can refinance. They can sell before things get bad. They can weather a hardship without
          losing the home. Every dollar of accelerated equity is a dollar of future optionality.
        </p>
        <ul class="service-list">
          <li>Guidance on paying down principal faster and reducing lifetime interest</li>
          <li>A living catalog of member discounts, rebates, and cashback partnerships</li>
          <li>Optional routing of realized savings toward principal reduction</li>
          <li>Ongoing equity education, available to members even after a refinance</li>
        </ul>

        <aside class="partner-card">
          <span class="partner-eyebrow">Featured member benefit</span>
          <h3>20% off all tax-prep services at Tax2Go DeSoto.</h3>
          <p>
            Equity Guardians members receive a 20% discount on every tax-preparation service offered by
            <a href="https://tax2godesoto.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tax2Go DeSoto, powered by Deduct Smart</a>.
            Present your active membership at booking to apply the discount.
          </p>
        </aside>

        <p class="phase-note">
          The curated catalog changes over time. Specific discounts, partners, and offers are not
          promised or guaranteed.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-illust illust-savings" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none">
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="80" fill="#E4F4F4"/>
          <path d="M60 130L100 90l30 30 30-50" stroke="#0F2E5C" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <circle cx="100" cy="90" r="6" fill="#0F2E5C"/>
          <circle cx="130" cy="120" r="6" fill="#4FB3B3"/>
          <circle cx="160" cy="70" r="6" fill="#C89A3E"/>
          <text x="100" y="170" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Fraunces, serif" font-size="14" fill="#0F2E5C" font-weight="500">SAVE · EARN · PROTECT</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="phase-02" class="section-alt">
    <div class="container service-block reverse reveal">
      <div class="service-copy">
        <span class="motto">
          <span class="motto-n">02</span>
          <span class="motto-t">When Hardship Threatens</span>
        </span>
        <h2>Legal defense, servicer communication, and every option on the table.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Hardship rarely announces itself. Job loss, income reduction, illness, disability, a
          death in the household, divorce, a missed payment, or even an anticipated missed payment
          are all signals that the family needs to move quickly. The moment one of those signals
          arrives, the team goes to work.
        </p>
        <p class="lede">
          The Legal Team reviews notices and deadlines, opens the right communications with the
          servicer, and analyzes what is available under the law and under the loan. The Case
          Manager keeps everyone informed. The goal at this phase is straightforward: keep the
          family in the home.
        </p>
        <ul class="service-list">
          <li>Legal advocacy and communication with your loan servicer</li>
          <li>Review of every notice, filing, and deadline before it becomes a problem</li>
          <li>Analysis of loan-modification and hardship-program options</li>
          <li>Negotiation of structured payment plans, where available</li>
          <li>Full legal representation if a foreclosure filing arrives</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="service-illust illust-shield" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none">
          <path d="M100 20 L170 45 V110 C170 145 140 175 100 190 C60 175 30 145 30 110 V45 Z" fill="#0F2E5C"/>
          <path d="M100 30 L160 52 V108 C160 138 135 163 100 178 C65 163 40 138 40 108 V52 Z" fill="none" stroke="#4FB3B3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4 4"/>
          <circle cx="100" cy="105" r="20" fill="#4FB3B3"/>
          <rect x="97" y="105" width="6" height="26" rx="2" fill="#4FB3B3"/>
          <path d="M90 100l7 8 15-16" stroke="white" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" fill="none"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="phase-03">
    <div class="container service-block reveal">
      <div class="service-copy">
        <span class="motto">
          <span class="motto-n">03</span>
          <span class="motto-t">When Keeping the Home Isn't Realistic</span>
        </span>
        <h2>Sell before foreclosure. Protect the family's credit and their equity.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Not every hardship can be reversed. If keeping the home is no longer realistic, the goal
          is not to let the family be erased at auction. The Buyer's Realtor moves to sell the home
          before foreclosure, while the family's credit is still strong and the Legal Team works to
          hold foreclosure at bay.
        </p>
        <p class="lede">
          A sale at market value protects far more than an auction ever will. Credit stays intact.
          Equity is preserved instead of forfeited. The family transitions into a rental with cash
          in hand to weather the hardship. And when their financial footing is restored, the same
          Realtor who helped them buy the first home is positioned to help them buy again.
        </p>
        <ul class="service-list">
          <li>Realtor-led sale before a foreclosure ever hits the family's record</li>
          <li>Market-value pricing instead of forced-auction pricing</li>
          <li>Preservation of surplus equity for the family, not the servicer</li>
          <li>Transition support into an appropriate rental home</li>
          <li>Positioning for a future purchase when the family recovers</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="service-illust illust-sale" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none">
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="80" fill="#E4F4F4"/>
          <path d="M40 130L100 70L160 130" stroke="#0F2E5C" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" fill="none"/>
          <rect x="70" y="110" width="60" height="45" fill="#0F2E5C" rx="2"/>
          <rect x="92" y="128" width="16" height="27" fill="#E4F4F4"/>
          <rect x="115" y="55" width="42" height="28" fill="#4FB3B3" rx="2"/>
          <text x="136" y="73" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Fraunces, serif" font-size="11" fill="white" font-weight="500">SOLD</text>
          <path d="M119 78L119 100" stroke="#0F2E5C" stroke-width="2"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="phase-04" class="section-alt">
    <div class="container service-block reverse reveal">
      <div class="service-copy">
        <span class="motto">
          <span class="motto-n">04</span>
          <span class="motto-t">When Foreclosure Still Happens*</span>
        </span>
        <h2>Foreclosure Recovery. We don't walk away.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          If a sale is not possible and foreclosure still happens, Equity Guardians does not
          consider the case closed. This is the phase most companies would walk away from. It is
          the phase our name is built around. The team continues to work, at or before the auction,
          to recover the home and put the family back in it.
        </p>
        <p class="lede">
          If the home can be recovered at or before auction, we attempt to refinance it back to the
          family at 0% interest on a new 30-year mortgage, protecting surplus equity and giving
          them a real chance to stay in the home they built a life in. Where the home cannot be
          recovered, we still pursue any surplus-equity the family is legally entitled to.
        </p>
        <ul class="service-list">
          <li>Pre-auction negotiation and buyback strategy</li>
          <li>Auction representation in eligible jurisdictions</li>
          <li>Refinance pathway and lender introductions, at 0% interest on a new 30-year mortgage</li>
          <li>Surplus-equity recovery filings where the home cannot be recovered</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="fine-print">
          * Foreclosure Recovery is a last-resort service. It is subject to auction outcomes,
          jurisdictional rules, and refinance qualification, and its results are not guaranteed.
          Past outcomes do not predict future results.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-illust illust-recovery" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none">
          <rect x="30" y="80" width="140" height="90" fill="#0F2E5C" rx="4"/>
          <path d="M30 80L100 30L170 80" stroke="#4FB3B3" stroke-width="4" fill="none" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <rect x="86" y="115" width="28" height="55" fill="#E4F4F4"/>
          <circle cx="108" cy="140" r="2" fill="#0F2E5C"/>
          <path d="M60 130L60 170 M140 130L140 170" stroke="#4FB3B3" stroke-width="2"/>
          <rect x="55" y="130" width="10" height="20" fill="#E4F4F4"/>
          <rect x="135" y="130" width="10" height="20" fill="#E4F4F4"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="representation" class="section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">The four components</span>
        <h2>Across every phase, four things always happen.</h2>
        <p class="lede lede-dark">
          The phases describe when. These four describe how. Whichever phase the family is in, the
          work runs on the same four rails.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-4 mt-4">
        {[
          { n: '01', t: 'Intervention',     b: 'Timely outreach to servicers, courts, and counterparties, with legal contact handled by the Legal Team and real estate matters by the Buyer\u2019s Realtor.' },
          { n: '02', t: 'Consulting',       b: 'Financial coordination by the Case Manager and legal counsel by the Legal Team.' },
          { n: '03', t: 'Education',        b: 'Clear explanation of every option before a decision is made.' },
          { n: '04', t: 'Representation',   b: 'Legal representation by the Legal Team, real estate representation by the Buyer\u2019s Realtor.' },
        ].map((s) => (
          <div class="step-dark reveal">
            <span class="step-n">{s.n}</span>
            <h3>{s.t}</h3>
            <p>{s.b}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Free to the buyer, for the life of the deed of trust</span>
        <h2>Every service, every attorney, at no cost to the buyer.</h2>
        <p class="lede">When you buy your home with an Equity Guardians affiliated Buyer's Realtor, coverage is included for as long as your original deed of trust exists.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary reveal">Find an affiliated realtor</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .service-block {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .service-block.reverse { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.3fr; }
  .service-block.reverse .service-copy { order: 2; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .service-block, .service-block.reverse { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
    .service-block.reverse .service-copy { order: 0; }
  }
  .service-copy h2 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .service-copy .lede + .lede { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .service-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .service-list li {
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--slate-700);
  }
  .service-list li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55rem;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--teal-500);
  }
  .service-illust svg {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 380px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 20px 40px rgba(15, 46, 92, 0.15));
  }

  /* Phase eyebrow: number + title, no middle dot */
  .service-copy .motto {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--teal-700);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .service-copy .motto-n {
    color: var(--teal-500);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .service-copy .motto-t { color: var(--teal-700); }

  .phase-note {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--slate-500);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .fine-print { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  /* How it works: three role cards */
  .roles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .roles-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .role-card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid var(--slate-200);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--teal-500);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(15, 46, 92, 0.05);
  }
  .role-eyebrow {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal-700);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .role-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--navy-900);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .role-card p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--slate-700);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .partner-card {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid var(--slate-200);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--teal-500);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(15, 46, 92, 0.06);
  }
  .partner-eyebrow {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal-700);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .partner-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--navy-900);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .partner-card p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--slate-700);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .partner-card a {
    color: var(--navy-800);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--teal-400);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .partner-card a:hover { color: var(--teal-700); border-color: var(--teal-700); }

  .step-dark {
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--teal-500);
  }
  .step-dark .step-n {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--teal-400);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .step-dark h3 { color: white; font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0.75rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .step-dark p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .lede-dark { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); }

  .cta-band { background: var(--sand-50); padding-block: 4.5rem; }
  .cta-inner {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .cta-inner h2 { max-width: 22ch; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .cta-inner .lede { margin-top: 0.75rem; }
</style>
